The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Indian Hotels set to expand

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 

 Mumbai, Aug. 5: Indian Hotels Company Ltd (IHCL) is planning to invest close to Rs 1,200 crore in expansion during this year. This is part of its plan to increase the total room capacity by about 30 per cent over the next couple of years.

 Announcing the companys expansion plans at its annual general meeting on Friday, chairman Ratan Tata said IHCL will increase its presence both in the luxury and budget segments. 

 The hotel chain is also looking to expand its reach abroad. In the coming months, the company is likely to increase its presence in Thailand and South Africa. 

 Taj Hotels will set up 30 budget hotels by the middle of 2008, he added.

 In December last year, IHCL acquired the W Hotel in Australia for Aus $36 million. 




